725778f-a.text:
109th Ave. (formerly Hawtree Creek Road), west from about 131st Street to 128th Street, where Hawtree Creek Road resumes its name and continues southward. This set of two views shows the W. Jellinghaus house of 1860 to 1873; later owned by Ditmars Van Siclen. Wyckoff Van Siclen was an occupant in 1922. In February 1925 the property was sold. St. Teresa's Catholic Church owned this
property in 1934.
1922.
Views 1 & 2.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
